items.title: Unable to allocate memory error
items.body:
I using this library via the TextPack package to detect duplicate company names. It has been fine for a few months but yesterday I got an out of memory error, "Unable to allocate 5.37 GiB for an array with shape (720117225,) and data type float64" at sparse_dot_topn/awesome_cossim_topn.py in awesome_cossim_topn, line 58. The code is:
```
data = np.empty(nnz_max, dtype=A.dtype)
```
The production environment is using a celery worker thread inside a docker container on AWS. If I restart the container and run it manually it works but fails again the next day.

There could be a memory leak (perhaps from another unrelated task) but I do not understand how this call to `np.empty` ever works - the task in the container only has 3584 MiB RAM, yet this call is requesting an array gigabytes in size. How come it doesn't crash each time?
